1. kubectl run <app-name> -> deploy an app
2. kubectl cluster-info -> to get info of cluster
3. kubectl get nodes -> List all nodes of a cluster.
4. kubectl get pods -> to get list of all pods
5. kubectl get pods -o wide -> It will show list of pods with details of node IP and name
6. kubectl describe pod <nameofpod> -> to get all details of a pod
7. kubectl delete pod <podname> -> to delete a pod
8. kubectl run redis --image=redis --dry-run=client -o yaml > redis.yaml
9. kubectl get replicaset
10. kubectl scale --replicas=6 -f replica.yaml -> to scale replicas
11. kubectl delete replicaset <name>
12. kubectl get all -> to get all details of deployment
13 kubectl apply -f <updated yaml file> -> for updating deployments
14 kubectl set image <file name> <name of container>=<newimage>
15 kubectl rollout status <deployment_name>
16 kubectl rollout histroy <deployment_name>
17 kubectl rollout undo <deployment_name>
18. kubectl edit deployment
19. kubectl describe service <name>
